<a name="WhatIsBatkeeping"></a>

<h2>What Is Batkeeping?</h2>

<p>
Batkeeping is a program for keeping records of weight and health of bats in a computer database.  The aim of the program is to replace the difficult to organize paper records of the old weight tracking system with a user friendly web application that hopefully makes everyone's lives a bit easier.
</p>

<p>
Some features:
<ul>
<li>Weight tracking with graphs</li>
<li>Automatic census keeping</li>
<li>Task management</li>
<li>Medical problem tracking</li>
</ul>
</p>

<p>
Batkeeping runs on <a href='http://rubyonrails.com'>Ruby on Rails</a>, an open source web framework for developing database driven web applications.  Batkeeping was built "in-lab" and is customized for our animal care protocols and standards.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name="SignIn"></a>

<h2>Sign in page</h2>
<p>
Before you are able to access the database you must sign in.  When you reach the signin page, just select your name from the drop down list and click "sign in". You should be taken directly to your user summary page.
</p>

<p>
If you do not have a user name, you can create one (this is the only part of the database that is accessable without signing in).  To create a user, click the link on the signin page which reads: "Add User".  Fill out the correct fields in the form and submit.  Then go back to the signin page and your newly created user should appear in the drop down list.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=MainMenu></a>

<h2>Main Menu</h2>

<a name=MyPage></a>

<h3>My Page</h3>

<p>
My Page takes you to your User Summary Page.  The User Summary Page is a quick summary of all the things in the database that relate to that user.
</p>
<p>
The User Summary Page lists:
<ul>
<li>A form for filling out the temperature and humidity in all the rooms in the database</li>
<li>The users' current jobs</li>
<li>The users' current cages</li>
<li>The users' bats' current medical problems (all bats with medical problems in cages that the user owns) OR all current medical problems in the database if one of the users' jobs is medical care</li>
<li>The users' tasks</li>
</ul>
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=ColonyStatus></a>

<h3>Colony Status</h3>

<p>
The colony status page is a listing of some statistics about the colony.  It contains a listing of the bats separated by room, the food needed by cage, and the bats in medical care.
</p>

<p>
There is a link at the top of the page that will take you to the Census Page for a given date (within the last 7 years).
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=CensusPage></a>

<h4>Census Page</h4>

<p>
The census page shows how many bats were in each room at any point in time.  It also lists the bats band numbers that were moved in or out of the room.  It also tracks whether all the room's tasks were completed on that day.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=AnimalCareStaff></a>

<h3>Animal Care Staff</h3>

<p>
The animal care staff takes you to a listing of the current animal care staff (weekday care, weekend care, and medical care).  All the users names are links to their respective user summary pages.  They will all share the tasks assigned to their job, but may have tasks that differ depending on the user's individually assigned tasks.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

