<a name=BatsMenu></a>

<h2>Bats Menu</h2>

<a name=ListBats></a>

<h3>List Bats</h3>

<p>
Lists the bats in the colony.  Click the headers to sort.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=NewBat></a>

<h3>New Bat</h3>

<p>
Creates a new bat.  Create a cage before creating a new bat.  Otherwise you'll have to carry the bat around with you.  You'll also need a species before creating a new bat.  Most likely this has already been done.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=WeighBat></a>

<h3>Weigh Bat</h3>

<p>
Brings up a list of bats to weigh.  Click the bat band and then enter the weight for the bat in the form.  A list of previous weights appear below as well as a link to graph the weights.  The after eating checkbox will automatically be checked if the bat's cage has been fed today, but you can uncheck it.</p>

<p>As you weigh the bat you can quickly add a medical problem if you find one for the bat.  If the bat needs to be moved or if you need to create a treatment for the medical problem, that will open a new page.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=MoveBat></a>

<h3>Move Bat</h3>

<p>
First select the cage that the bat(s) is/are coming from, then the particular bat(s), then click select bats, and then the destination cage.  Once you click submit at the bottom of the page you will be taken to a series of steps for modifying the weighing tasks and feedings tasks of the old and new cage of the bat(s) you moved.  This action automatically updates the census page if the bat is moved between rooms.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=CagesMenu></a>

<h2>Cages Menu</h2>

<a name=ListCages></a>

<h3>List Cages</h3>

<p>
List the cages in the colony.  Click the headers to sort the cages.  This is where you deactivate a cage (destroy).  You must move all bats out of the cage before the cage is destroyed.  We don't want homeless bats.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=NewCage></a>

<h3>New Cage</h3>

<p>
Creates a new cage.  You need a room to put the cage in before creating the cage.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=WeighCage></a>

<h3>Weigh Cage</h3>

<p>
Brings up a list of cages to weigh.  Once you choose the cage a list of bats will appear.  Choose the bat to weigh and enter the bats weight in the form.  Follow the same procedures as you would if you were <a href=#WeighBat>weighing a single bat</a>.
</p>

<a href=#top>Top</a>

<a name=MoveCage></a>

<h3>Move Cage</h3>

<p>
Brings up a list of cages for you to choose to move.  Then choose a room, and then click Move Cage.
</p>

